title: Girls Soccer Roundup: Warriors down Lancers
text:
Girls Soccer Roundup: Warriors down Lancers Advocate staff report 7:05 p.m. EDT October 3, 2015 File photo CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Watkins Memorial 5, Lakewood 3 
Grace Berry and Rachel Lawwell each scored a pair of goals for Watkins Memorial (5-6-2, 4-1-0) in a Licking County League win at Lakewood Saturday. Dana Berry also scored a goal for the Warriors and Theresa LaGreca and Caitlyn Smith each had an assist. Elizabeth Romshe had five saves. 
Cheyenne Brooks scored two goals for the Lancers (6-6-1, 1-3-1) and Abby Gregg had one. Becca Madrid had an assist and Rylea Amspaugh had 18 saves. 
Licking Valley 2, Coshocton 2 
Heidi Hall and Lauryn Greer each scored a goal for Licking Valley (4-8-0) Saturday in a nonleague game at Coshocton. Ashley Schmoll had an assist for the Panthers and Kelsea Hagans had 10 saves. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RnD4UQ More Stories
